{"lemma":"رَبِيعِ","slug":"رَبِيعِ","root":"ر.ب.ع","root_slug":"ر-ب-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ب-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14545","n14546"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"spring (season)","examples":[{"text":"تَتَفَتَّحُ الْأَزْهَارُ مَعَ قُدُومِ الرَّبِيعِ","english":"Flowers bloom as spring comes"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"spring grain"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"spring vegetation, verdure, pasture"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ra.biːʕ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14545","headword_ar":"رَبِيعٌ","root":"rbE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruboEN","text_ar":"رُبْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places.       -A2-  It has also a twofold application; to months and to seasons: and it has a twofold application to months; denoting"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two months,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"next"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SafarN","text_ar":"صَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) and they say, (Msb,) one should only say, in speaking of them,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahoru rabiyEK AlA^aw~alu","text_ar":"شَهْرُ رَبِيعٍ الاَوَّلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahoru rabiyEK AlA=xirN","text_ar":"شَهْرُ رَبِيعٍ الا=خِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) [but in the margin of the copy of the S which I have here followed, I find it stated that in the handwriting of the author the former is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$hr rbyEi AlAwl","text_ar":"شهر ربيعِ الاول"},{"kind":"text","text":"(with a single kesreh, and with no syll. sign to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAwl","text_ar":"الاول"},{"kind":"text","text":"); and in another copy of the S I find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$hru rbyE AlAwli","text_ar":"شهرُ ربيع الاولِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahru rabyE AlA=xir","text_ar":"شَهرُ رَبيع الا=خِر"},{"kind":"text","text":";] with the addition of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$hr","text_ar":"شهر"},{"kind":"text","text":": but it is allowable to say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahoru rabiyEi AlA^aw~ali","text_ar":"شَهْرُ رَبِيعِ الاَوَّلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahoru rabiyEi AlA=xiri","text_ar":"شَهْرُ رَبِيعِ الا=خِرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$hr","text_ar":"شهر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is necessarily added in order to discriminate between the months thus called and the season called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbyE","text_ar":"ربيع"},{"kind":"text","text":": Az says, the Arabs mention all the months without the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$hr","text_ar":"شهر"},{"kind":"text","text":"except the two months of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbyE","text_ar":"ربيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the month of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramaDaAn","text_ar":"رَمَضَان"},{"kind":"text","text":": and they say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahoraA rabiyEK","text_ar":"شَهْرَا رَبِيعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ohuru rabiyEK","text_ar":"اَشْهُرُ رَبِيعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uhuwru rabiyEK","text_ar":"شُهُورُ رَبِيعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) these months were thus called because, when they received this name, they occurred in the season when the earth produced herbage. (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jmd","text_ar":"جمد"},{"kind":"text","text":".) It has a twofold application also to seasons;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~abiyEu AlA^aw~alu","text_ar":"الرَّبِيعُ الاَوَّلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The season in which the truffles and the blossoms come,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,) and this is [also called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyEu AlkalaA^i","text_ar":"رَبِيعُ الكَلَاِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the rabeea of the herbage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"properly called"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the spring of Arabia"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~abiyEu Alv~aAniY","text_ar":"الرَّبِيعُ الثَّانِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The season in which fruits ripen;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;) [also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyEu Alv~imaAri","text_ar":"رَبِيعُ الثِّمَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] but some people call this"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~abiyEu AlA^aw~alu","text_ar":"الرَّبِيعُ الاَوَّلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, TA;) and the season which follows the winter, and in which the truffles and the blossoms come, they call"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~abiyEu Alv~aAniY","text_ar":"الرَّبِيعُ الثَّانِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but all of them agree that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xariyf","text_ar":"خَرِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"autumn"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~abiyEu","text_ar":"الرَّبِيعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": AHn says, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two divisions of the winter"},{"kind":"text","text":"[by which he means the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"half-year commencing at the autumnal equinox"},{"kind":"text","text":"] are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyEaAni","text_ar":"رَبِيعَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the former being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyEu AlmaA='i waAlA^amoTaAr i","text_ar":"رَبِيعُ المَا=ءِ وَالاَمْطَار ِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the rabeea of the water and the rains,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in which the rain called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwasomiY~","text_ar":"الوَسْمِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is termed the first of the rains, commences]; and the second being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyEu Aln~abaAti","text_ar":"رَبِيعُ النَّبَاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyEu AlkalaA^i","text_ar":"رَبِيعُ الكَلَاِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the rabeea of the herbage"},{"kind":"text","text":"], because the herbage therein attains to its last stage: and he adds, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyEN","text_ar":"رَبِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied by the Arabs to the whole"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"winter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning, again, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"half-year commencing at the autumnal equinox,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] because of the moisture, or rain: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the year consists of six seasons;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(so in the K; but in the S, “ and I heard Abu-l-Ghowth say, the Arabs make the year to be six seasons; ”)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two months thereof are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~abiyEu AlA^aw~alu","text_ar":"الرَّبِيعُ الاَوَّلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and two months,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SayofN","text_ar":"صَيْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and two months,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qayoZN","text_ar":"قَيْظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two months,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbyE","text_ar":"ربيع"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlvAnY","text_ar":"الثانى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in a copy of the S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyEN Alv~AnY","text_ar":"رَبِيعٌ الثّانى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in another copy of the S, [but in the margin of this latter, I find it stated that in the handwriting of the author it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbyEu AlvAnY","text_ar":"ربيعُ الثانى"},{"kind":"text","text":", without tenween,]) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~abiyEu Alv~aAniY","text_ar":"الرَّبِيعُ الثَّانِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and two months,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xariyfN","text_ar":"خَرِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and two months,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$itaA='N","text_ar":"شِتَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) Az relates, with respect to the seasons and divisions of the year, on the authority of Aboo-Yahyà Ibn-Kibáseh, who possessed very great knowledge thereof, that the year consists of four seasons; namely,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~abiyEu AlA^aw~alu","text_ar":"الرَّبِيعُ الاَوَّلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which the vulgar call"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxariyfu","text_ar":"الخَرِيفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The autumn"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; then"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~itaA='u","text_ar":"الشِّتَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the winter"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; then"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~ayofu","text_ar":"الصَّيْفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~abiyEu AlA=xiru","text_ar":"الرَّبِيعُ الا=خِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~aAniY","text_ar":"الثَّانِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the spring"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; then"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqayoZu","text_ar":"القَيْظُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the summer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hot season"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: all this is what the Arabs in the desert say:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbyE","text_ar":"ربيع"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is with the Persians the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xryf","text_ar":"خريف"},{"kind":"text","text":", he says,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commences on the third of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayoluwl","text_ar":"اَيْلُول"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"September O. S."},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$itaA='","text_ar":"شِتَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", on the third of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAnuwn AlA^aw~al","text_ar":"كَانُون الاَوَّل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[December O. S.]; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Syf","text_ar":"صيف"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1019},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is with the Persians the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbyE","text_ar":"ربيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the fifth of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=*aAr","text_ar":"ا=ذَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"March O. S."},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qyZ","text_ar":"قيظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is with the Persians the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Syf","text_ar":"صيف"},{"kind":"text","text":", on the fourth of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaziyraAn","text_ar":"حَزِيرَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[June O. S.]: and Aboo-Yahyà adds,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbyE","text_ar":"ربيع"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the people of El-' Irák agrees with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbyE","text_ar":"ربيع"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Persians, which is after the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$tA'","text_ar":"شتاء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"winter"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and which is the season of the flowers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"roses, and is the most temperate of the seasons"},{"kind":"text","text":": the people of El-' Irák, he says, have rain in all the winter, and have abundance of herbage in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xryf","text_ar":"خريف"},{"kind":"text","text":", which the Arabs call"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlrbyE AlAw~l","text_ar":"الربيع الاوّل"},{"kind":"text","text":": and Az says, the quarter of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xryf","text_ar":"خريف"},{"kind":"text","text":"is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xryf","text_ar":"خريف"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the fruits are gathered therein; and the Arabs call it"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbyE","text_ar":"ربيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the first rain [which is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwasomiY~","text_ar":"الوَسْمِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] falls therein. (TA.) The pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbyE","text_ar":"ربيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arobiEapN","text_ar":"اَرْبِعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of pauc.] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arobiEaA='u","text_ar":"اَرْبِعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of mult.] (S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaAEN","text_ar":"رِبَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (AHn, K;) or the first of these is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbyE AlklA^","text_ar":"ربيع الكلا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, Yaakoob, S, Msb, K) and of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbyE","text_ar":"ربيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the months; (Fr, Msb;) but the second is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbyE","text_ar":"ربيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jadowalN","text_ar":"جَدْوَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", to be explained below. (Fr, Yaakoob, S, Msb, K.) Hence the phrase in a supplication, mentioned in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aall~`hum~a A@joEali AlquroA=na rabiyEa qalobiY","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُمَّ ا@جْعَلِ القُرْا=نَ رَبِيعَ قَلْبِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O God, make Thou the Kur-án to be the life,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ease, of my heart"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; because the heart of man becomes lively, or at ease, in the season called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyE","text_ar":"رَبِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Hence also, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw Alr~abiyEi","text_ar":"اَبُو الرَّبِيعِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hudohud","text_ar":"هُدْهُد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hoopoe"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (K;) because it appears with the [season called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbyE","text_ar":"ربيع"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [See also, respecting the seasons &c., the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zamanN","text_ar":"زَمَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rain in the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"season called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabyE","text_ar":"رَبيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the half-year commencing at the autumnal equinox,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(which includes what is really the spring of Arabia, called “ the rabeea of the herbage, ”) accord. to a statement of AHn cited above, and accord. to what is stated on the authority of AZ voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawo'N","text_ar":"نَوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K:) or [only, accord. to some,] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rain which is after the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasomiY~","text_ar":"وَسْمِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and after which is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sayof","text_ar":"صَيْف"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and then the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hamiym","text_ar":"حَمِيم"},{"kind":"text","text":": or, accord. to AHn,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rain whenever it comes"},{"kind":"text","text":": Az says, I have heard the Arabs call thus the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first rain falling upon the earth in the days of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xariyf","text_ar":"خَرِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"autumn"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) the pl. [of pauc.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arobiEapN","text_ar":"اَرْبِعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaAEN","text_ar":"رِبَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (AHn, TA.) [See also, respecting the rains, the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zamanN","text_ar":"زَمَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Herbage; green herbage which the beasts eat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) [properly] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage that is produced by the first rain in the quarter which is called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyE","text_ar":"رَبِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and which is commonly called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xariyf","text_ar":"خَرِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"autumn"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zmn","text_ar":"زمن"},{"kind":"text","text":",) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continuing its growth during the winter-quarter, which is also called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyE","text_ar":"رَبِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and which includes, as stated above, what is really the spring of Arabia, called “ the rabeea of the herbage, ” wherein,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as AHn says,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the herbage attains to its last stage"},{"kind":"text","text":": it seems generally to mean the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spring-herbage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is earlier or later in different latitudes:] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroibEapN","text_ar":"اَرِْبعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [Hence,] a poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yadaAka yadN rabiyEu Aln~aAsi fiyhaA\n                      \n                     \n                        wafiY AlA^uxoraY Al$~uhuwru mina AlHaraAmi"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thy two hands are such that"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one hand has in it the means of the plentiful subsistence of mankind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and in the other are the sacred months,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the other is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that which causes"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"security, and safeguard, and the preservation of what is to be regarded as sacred and inviolable."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [Compare Proverbs iii. 16.] ―         -b4-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rivulet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"streamlet;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jadowalN","text_ar":"جَدْوَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahorN","text_ar":"نَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahorN SagiyrN","text_ar":"نَهْرٌ صَغِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Har p. 402:) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rivulet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"streamlet, that runs to palmtrees"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyEu Als~aAqiY","text_ar":"رَبِيعُ السَّاقِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", a subst prefixed to its epithet, occurring in a trad., (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the river"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rivulet"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that waters seed-produce"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arobiEaA='u","text_ar":"اَرْبِعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, Yaakoob, S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riboEaAnN","text_ar":"رِبْعَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) A poet says, describing one drinking much,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"fuwhu rabiyEN wakaf~uhu qadaHN"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His mouth is a river"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and his hand is a bowl"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b5-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A share,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion, of water for"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"irrigating"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whatever it be"},{"kind":"text","text":": or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a share,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion, thereof for the quarter of a day"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"night;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this is not of valid authority. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lifulaAnK mino h`*aA","text_ar":"لِفُلَانٍ مِنْ هٰذَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaA='i rabiyEN","text_ar":"المَا=ءِ رَبِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) or, as in some copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY","text_ar":"فِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To such a one belongs a share,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion, of this water"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for irrigating land"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b6-  The dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyEN","text_ar":"رَبِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rubay~iEN","text_ar":"رُبَيِّعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","Mgh","IDrd"]},{"entry_id":"n14546","headword_ar":"رُبَيِّعٌ","root":"rbE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rubaAEN","text_ar":"رُبَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":       -A2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyEN","text_ar":"رَبِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}